    "body": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nSeveral zh_CN translations were marked fuzzy with wrong or placeholder msgstr.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nFix fuzzy entries, preserve format specifiers, use full-width punctuation.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-16T09:16:58Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39109#discussion_r3091707449"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/39109"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3091707449"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This doesn't look correct. This is for `:argdelete`:\n```\n:argd[elete] {pattern} ...\t\t*:argd* *:argdelete* *E480* *E610*\n\t\t\tDelete files from the argument list that match the\n\t\t\t{pattern}s.  {pattern} is used like a file pattern,\n\t\t\tsee |file-pattern|.  \"%\" can be used to delete the\n\t\t\tcurrent entry.\n\t\t\tThis command keeps the currently edited file, also\n\t\t\twhen it's deleted from the argument list.\n\t\t\tExample: >\n\t\t\t\t:argdel *.obj\n```",
            "commit_id": "981c13be98c2340514e7ac3b22951e833a97d27b",
            "created_at": "2026-04-16T08:16:56Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -45,9 +45,8 @@ msgid \"E165: Cannot go beyond last file\"\n msgstr \"E165: 无法切换，已是最后一个文件\"\n \n #: ../arglist.c:782\n-#, fuzzy\n msgid \"E610: No argument to delete\"\n-msgstr \"E144: :z 不接受非数字的参数\"\n+msgstr \"E610: delete 没有参数\"",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39109#discussion_r3091707449",
